Rick became a valued colleague during my time at VDS, primarily for his attitude toward success - he understood that we needed to get way outside of the box to get the best results. I watched him launch two big local brands into search engine prominence and often consulted him on my own tactics and ideas. This is the person they're talking about when you hear "changemaker" and "thought leader".Another great component to his contributions was the fact that he was experienced with running his own agency in the past. It was quite helpful to have the grounded, seasoned voice of reason when it came to a more elaborate plan.I miss Rick, frankly. He is a mentor, a big thinker, and a person I endorse without reservation.
